data.text:
The Candystripes will be looking to push for the Title once more this season after being the only challenges to Rovers last season, and will be in fine form off the back of an FAI Cup win to close out the year.

They are the only club located in Northern Ireland to compete in the SSE Airtricity League and have two league titles to their name in 1988-89 and 1996-97 with five FAI cup successes, the most recent in 2012. The club do hold the record for most League Cup victories with 12, most recently of course in 2022.
